  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Type 2 diabetes mellitus

          -  Diet treated and/or subjects in monotherapy with sulphonylurea or repaglinide

          -  HbA1c for diet treated subjects 6.5-12%, both inclusive

          -  HbA1c for sulphonylurea or repaglinide treated subjects maximum 10%

          -  Body mass index (BMI) at least 27 kg/m^2

          -  Euthyroid subjects

          -  Fasting blood glucose 7-14 mmol/l

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Impaired liver function

          -  Impaired renal function

          -  Cardiac problems

          -  Uncontrolled treated/untreated hypertension

          -  Recurrent severe hypoglycaemia as judged by the Investigator

          -  Known or suspected allergy to trial product or related products

          -  Use of any drug (except for OHAs (oral hypoglycaemic agents), which in the
             Investigator's opinion could interfere with the glucose level or body weight. Stable
             doses, for 3 months or greater, of thyroid hormone replacement are allowed
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
